<h1>Paradoxical feeling</h1>
<p>Imagine a transporter that has a 99% chance of doing nothing and a 1% chance of working correctly. It can make transport attempts 1,000 times per second.</p>

<p>You have 3,000,000 of these working together.</p>

<p>How many transports complete after 1 second?</p>

<p>3,000,000 * (1-0.99) = 30,000</p>

